<h2 id="_1_info_revenues_by_item_groups">1. 1) Info: revenues by item groups</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic shows the <strong>revenue</strong> that was generated by a particular <strong>group of items</strong> that were purchased during a selected <strong>time span</strong> and that are included in sales orders that fall into a selected <strong>sales order status</strong> range. As an alternative to selecting a certain predefined time span, you can also choose an individual <strong>start</strong> and <strong>end date</strong>. Default setting for the <strong>time span</strong>: the <strong>last 10 days</strong>. Default setting of the <strong>status section</strong>: from <strong>status 1</strong> to <strong>status 7</strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This statistic is available <strong>starting with plentymarkets version 4.501</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_2_details_about_the_statistic">2. 2) Details about the statistic</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <strong>number of sales orders</strong> and the corresponding <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> will be displayed for those items that were filtered with the options <strong>marking 1</strong> and <strong>marking 2</strong> and that were generated within the selected <strong>time span</strong>. If this group of items did not generate any revenue on a particular day, then no data will be displayed for this day. The <strong>revenue in Euro</strong> that the group of items generated during a particular <strong>time span</strong> and the <strong>number of sales orders</strong> that correspond to this revenue will be displayed as <strong>information in a mouseover</strong> (see image 1). In this statistic you can see, e.g. how the revenue changed over time for a group of items that have a particular marking.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock note">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-note" title="Note"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title"><strong>Show details (mouseover)</strong></div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Point your <strong>cursor</strong> at one of the elements in the statistic in order to see <strong>details</strong> about that particular element.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Tip</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In image 1, you can see that the particular <strong>group of items</strong> specified by the markings corresponded to a total <strong>revenue</strong> of <strong>808.98 Euros</strong> on <strong>January 22nd, 2013</strong> and that this revenue was generated by <strong>6 sales orders</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
